Reference

All functions

add_bbi_args()

Add new babylon args to model

add_config()

Joins config log tibble onto a matching run log tibble

apply_indices() block()

Add parameter indices to a label tibble

as_model()

Convert object to `bbi_.model_type_model`

bbi_current_release()

current release

bbi_dry_run()

Babylon dry_run

bbi_exec()

Executes a babylon call (`bbi ...`) with processx::process$new()

bbi_help()

Executes (`bbi --help`) with bbi_exec and prints the output string

bbi_init()

Executes (`bbi init`) with bbi_exec() in specified directory

bbi_version()

bbi version

build_bbi_param_list()

Builds list of unique parameter sets for multiple model bbi calls

build_matrix_indices()

Builds matrix indices labels

build_path_from_mod_obj()

Builds the absolute path to a file in the output directory from components of the `bbi_.model_type_model` object

check_bbi_exe()

Checks that a bbi binary is present at the path passed to .bbi_exe_path

check_file() tail_output() tail_lst()

Reads the head and tail of specified file and prints it the console and/or returns it as a character vector.

check_lst_file()

Helper function to look for .lst function in a directory

check_nonmem_args()

Checks that all passed NONMEM command line args are valid and formats

check_nonmem_table_output() check_grd() check_ext()

Checks nonmem output file that's a whitespace-delimited file (for instance .grd or .ext)

check_output_dir()

List files in the output directory to glance at where the process is

check_status_code()

Checks status code from processx process

clean_ctl()

Parse control stream to a named list of the blocks

combine_directory_path()

Build absolute path from a directory and path

combine_list_objects()

Combines two named lists. By default, shared keys are overwritten by that key in .new_list Any S3 classes will be inherited with those from .new_list given precedence.

config_log()

Parses model config.json outputs into a log tibble

copy_control_stream()

Copy a NONMEM control stream file

copy_model_from() copy_nonmem_model_from()

Generic S3 method from iterating on models.

create_model_object() create_summary_object() create_process_object() create_run_log_object()

Creates S3 object of class `bbi_.model_type_model` from list with `MODEL_REQ_INPUT_KEYS`

enforce_length()

Helper to enforce length of a list element

find_model_file_path()

helper to find valid model file and return ctl_ext(.path) by default if not found

format_cmd_args()

Formats command line args from a named list to a string as it would be passed on the command line

get_model_id()

Helper to strip path and extension from model file to get only model identifier

get_path_from_object() get_model_path() get_output_dir() get_yaml_path()

Get path from bbi object

is_diag()

Check if diagonal index or not

model_summary() nonmem_summary()

S3 generic for getting model summary

modify_model_field() add_tags() replace_tags() add_decisions() replace_decisions() add_based_on() replace_based_on() replace_description()

Modify field in model object

new_ext() ctl_ext() mod_ext() yaml_ext()

helpers that strip extension then add a diffent type

new_model()

Create new model object by specifying relevant information as arguments Also creates necessary YAML file for using functions like `add_tags()` and `run_log()` later.

param_estimates()

S3 generic for parsing parameter estimate table

param_labels()

Extract parameter labels for report tables, etc.

parse_args_list()

Combines NONMEM args that were passed into the function call with args that were parsed from a model yaml

parse_param_comment() parse_same_block()

extract labels from comments in raw ctl string

plot_nonmem_table_df() plot_grd() plot_ext()

Creates a line plot of the wide-format tibble output from check_nonmem_table_output

print_nonmem_args()

Prints all valid arguments to pass in submit_nonmem_model(.args=list())

rbabylon

RBabylon

read_model()

Creates a model object from a YAML model file

reconcile_yaml() check_yaml_in_sync()

Reconcile model object with YAML file

replace_bbi_args()

Replaces babylon args to model

run_log()

Parses model yaml and outputs into a tibble that serves as a run log. Future releases will incorporate more diagnostics and parameter estimates, etc. from the runs into this log.

run_log_entry()

Create a run log row from a `bbi_.model_type_model` object

safe_read_model()

Read in model YAML with error handling

save_model_yaml()

Saves a model model object to a yaml file

set_model_directory()

Set global model directory option

submit_model() submit_nonmem_model()

S3 generic method for submit_model

submit_models() submit_nonmem_models()

S3 generic method for submit_models

suppressSpecificWarning()

Suppress a warning that matches `.regexpr`

use_bbi()

Installing bbi
